            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Don't recommend for primary school admissions. Waste of money and though school is supposed to teach in English medium my child found it very pathetic as she learned in Scotland school.\nToday on annual day, they kept my child waiting for 5 hours and still 2.5 hrs to go for her round of performance. Teacher asked to come at 2.30 pm and her team performance was scheduled at 9.30 pm onward. No snacks or drinks arranged by school. We asked to release my daughter and she'll be back at 9.o pm but the class teacher swaymsudha argued and called principal Kalpana mam where she was also adamant and finally I have to take my daughter to home at 7.50 pm.\nVery poor time management and still sarcastic way of speaking to parents even after committing a wrongdoing.\nIf you want to Waste time and money in return of poor performance of your ward then you are free to choose this school.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
