          },
          "datePublished": "2022-12-17",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "3",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "It’s okay school if you are looking at pure English speaking staff. Though they are most experienced but prefer teaching in Hindi or Marathi at times . However better than Dada Gujar school in Mohammad wadi road . The classes happen on time and PTM experience was just okay . If you want a budget school compromising quality of spoken English - then go for it . You won’t regret though ! The school approach is still in their 90s led by an opportunist institution head and politician. But good for the people who can’t afford costly education outside .",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
